cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the relationship between two optimization methods, stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and evolution strategy (ES), in the context of deep reinforcement learning (RL) and supervised learning on the MNIST dataset. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY) in the RL context, which are less prominent but still relevant sub-categories.
